In order to excise 59 seconds worth of video/audio from "NL.mp4" to output
file "edited_Nightline.mp4" starting at 1 minute into the original clip,
chant

ffmpeg -ss 00:01:00 -t 00:00:59 -i "NL.mp4" -qscale 1 -acodec copy -vcodec copy "edited_Nightline.mp4"

In order to generate a silent movie in which the input audio track is
ignored, use ffmpeg's "-an" flag:

ffmpeg -ss 00:00:00 -t 00:00:53 -i "YouTube_clip_0002.mp4" -qscale 1
-vcodec copy -an "silent_YouTube_clip_0002.mp4"

ffmpeg -i Obama_April16_am.mp4 -qscale 1 -vcodec copy -an "silent_Obama_April16_am.mp4"

In order to fade input audio track after 8 secs down to no volume, we
downloaded to BEAST and compiled ffmpeg-1.2.1 on 6/10/13:

./ffmpeg -i YouTube_clip_0002.mp4 -qscale 1 -strict -2 -vcodec copy \
-af "afade=t=out:st=0:d=8" YouTube_clip2_8sec_audiofade.mp4


