In order to get highest quality JPG stills from an input movie, include 
'-qscale 1' into the ffmpeg extraction command:

ffmpeg -i day1_flt1.mpg -r 1 -f image2 -qscale 1 ./jpg_frames/frame-%05d.jpg

=======================================================================

On 2/17/12, we wanted to convert a PBS NewsHour "News Wrap" clip to a set
of PNG files.  We first loaded up the file from Youtube.  It saved a cached
copy as a temporary flash file in /tmp.  We renamed the /tmp file as
NewsWarp_Jun15_2011.flv.  We then copied the file over to our ROBOT laptop
(Ubuntu 10.04) and ran the following ffmpeg command to extract its frames:


  ffmpeg -i NewsWrap_Jun15_2011.flv -r 5 -f image2 ./png/frame-%04d.png

